      {
        "contents": "what career to do i want, how does IS get me there, and what can i bring to the IS college are the three main application pieces \nWhat career do I want? Fuck if I know, but talk about how information influences it in a general sense. Talk about the TikTok research and the mind controlled drone and how impactful you think information is\n\nHow does IS get me there? Talk about how important the mindsets you learned in IS101 and 202 are. Go into philosophy shit a lil. And then talk about how important data analysis is and how those skills will give you what you want. \n\nWhat culture I can bring to IS? Talk about eskates. That is niche but definitely culture and also shows participation. \n\nNext steps: look at application, write the questions, chatgpt, you'll be solid\n\nAlright so after a look at the questions, I want to frame my application around IS is about mixing information systems with humans, and I am passionate about that. It shows through my web extension and my app and my home server. This is for the first 4 essays. Next essay is about how I struggled with previous semester, and how I took HK109 and how I'm mixing that with technology to hold myself accountable. Next two are chatgpted, and last one is about internship. For the one about what I do  for extracirriculars, it does tie into how the dude talked about what culture I bring to the IS college. I can talk about eskates and how that became a major part of me.  Talk about skateboarding, surfskates, maybe the startup? ",
        "deleted": false,
